				<td colspan="2"><span>I'll second that!  I avoided playing in the chests until lvl 52 when I got my remove curse song.  Before that people were just flat out refused to let me even inspect a chest.  So I get my song, and of course then it takes 3 ldon's for me to even find a chest.  Wizard takes a look, no dice.  Can't open it.  I go up sense traps on it, and BAM one nasty arse poison curse goes off.  Well, having been prepared for curses (bad planning on my part) I had to sit down and mem my remove poison/disease song.  
<br />

<br />
Get that memmed, and hit the cleric with it first.  Want to make sure I get him cured, I watch my life drain as I'm singing on him.  Finish him, target myself.  3 pulses later (or so it seemed at the time) I am cured.  Cleric and I proceeded to cure everyone else then.  Last cure went off with the person at like 23% life.  Oops.  Lesson learned.  Have BOTH songs memorized before you play with the chest!
<br />

<br />
On a side note, if the wiz and I couldn't open it, would it have taken a cleric to do so?</span></td>
